Create the Data Cloud Objects to Connect Third-Party Data

Use the Segment Intelligence setup flow to add the required data model objects (DMOs), and map the data streams to the DMOs for Google Ads and Meta Ads data.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience	Available in: Enterprise and Unlimited Editions


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To manage Data Cloud:	Data Cloud Admin permission set
To add the required Segment Intelligence DMOs:	Data Cloud Admin permission set
NOTE

After you run the automation you can’t edit the DMOs or the mappings. Editing impacts the accuracy of the data displayed in the dashboards.

On the Segment Intelligence setup page, go to Third-Party Data Prerequisites.
To create the necessary DMOs and data mappings, click Run Automation.
These DMOs are created for Google ads and Meta ads.
Media Conversion
Media Performance
Ad Group
Ad Group Segment
Meta Ads Audience

You can view the DMOs, and mappings in their respective tabs in Data Cloud. If you don’t see the tabs, click More and search for it by name.
